Package: weasel
Type: Package
Title: Wave-Based Extraction and Selection for Longitudinal Data
Version: 0.4.0
Authors@R:
    person("Siard", "van den Bosch", , "siardvandenbosch@me.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"))
Description: Turns wave-and-respondent selection in longitudinal panels
    into an explicit, reproducible workflow. Provides a scope-based
    pipeline for wave pattern analysis and a planning interface for
    scenario-based respondent selection with configurable missingness
    tolerances, interior-gap constraints, and endpoint requirements.
    Wave grids may be consecutive integers or the observed schedule
    (e.g. biennial panels). Includes tolerance-sensitivity and
    attrition-selectivity diagnostics, plus a generator of
    ready-to-paste methods-section justification text. A full workflow
    guide is available at <https://siardv.github.io/weasel/>.
